e poor GMs responsible for providing this &quot;dynamic content&quot; will be caught in the middle, and I think things are going to go rapidly downhill.  Might be wrong, but this is my prediction.  If Legends is no more successful than FV, but requires all the support they are lumping into it, I think it may die a premature death.<br><br>Now, if Legends does fail as a premium service, Verant will be left with all their coding for such neat things as personal webpages, maps of Norrath, etc., and will have nothing to do with it.  This stuff doesn't require dynamic support, it's just coding.  And if the premium service dies they'll end up rolling it into their general service because there will be nothing else to do with it.  So that's why boycotting Legends is good not only on general principle, but in order for us all to get what they are trying to sell only to a priviledged few.  I wouldn't leave FV anyway, not for any premium service, not even if it was free, but give this all some time to iron out and it might be right in the end.  Even if Verant doesn't have a clue beforehand, sometimes, they can feel the landslide of player opinion building.<br><br>Valquiss <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=valquisssilverpalm>Valquiss Silverpalm</A> at: 2/2/02 5:15:05 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubanegrivm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Banegrivm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 404<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/2/02 5:19:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1265.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br>