 Sony is attempting to maximize their revenue from this product.  For example, Big Tobacco knows (though they'll never admit) that tobacco is addictive.  They have worked out the attrition levels at which people quit smoking in the face of price increases.  EQ is no different.  If they quadruple the price for the hard-core addicts, and only 10% leave, they enjoy a 360% increase in revenue.  Not bad.<br><br>Third, Sony is feeling out the market for their upcomming products (i.e. Star Wars Galaxies).  If the Legends servers max out right away, and there is demand for yet more, Sony knows it can come out with a fairly hefty monthy fee subscription for their new products.<br><br>The thing to consider is this.  Should Legends succeed, we may all be facing higher subscription fees for basic EQ as well for new products.  Furthermore, it would catapult Sony farther ahead of any other developer (with the increased revenue they will enjoy), increasing the barriers to entry for the MMORPG market.<br><br>My final comment is this - even though it has been stated before.  If you think the Legends server is going to be any sort of RP paradise...think again.  It will be the very essence and distillation of powergaming/loot-hunting.  And for the roleplayers, the double-damning thing will be that it will work and future products may be geared accordingly.<br><br>Rexfelix<br>Agent of the Balance <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaladominus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maladominus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/2/02 6:16:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1265.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Alright...</span><hr size=1> I'm ambivalent to this thing right now. <br><br>My instinct says that financially, the Legends servers will do OK for Verant. There will be enough people who will jump at the opportunity to want to play this sort of server. <br><br>Think about it. <br><br>Statistically, over 400,000 EQ subscribers. I was quoted that this figure is now around 430,000 after the recent Christmas season and all the first-time players that SoL brought in. I also don't buy into the &quot;decline phase&quot; theory. At least the statistics do not show any decline at this moment. Tho I admit that EQ does have a surge of new competition (DAoC, etc) that will make customer growth slower for Verant in the coming year. They know that. We know that. Everyone knows that. <br><br>Verant is targeting around 8,000 players for the Legends servers to meet their goal, right? <br><br>8,000 players out of 400,000 is a mere tiny 2% <br><br>Two percent of the total. They only need 2% of Everquest players to try out the Legends server....and Verant will have already achieved their goal. This goal is very much attainable for them. <br><br>The Pros: <br><br>If Verant meets their goal, then the Legends server is simply a revenue stream. End result is that Verant will have extra pocket money to upgrade and improve all existing EQ projects. They will also have extra money to hire more developers and programmers. They may even have enough money to actually upgrade their existing hardware, servers and connections too. That's a long term benefit for everyone. <br><br>The Cons: <br><br>Short term, the investment needed to make the Legends server work means that staffing and funding normally allocated for NORMAL servers (including FV) may possibly be underfunded, understaffed, or put by the wayside.... and thus diverted into the Legends servers. <br><br>Right now, it's not necessarily a doom and gloom scenario. Personally I doubt I will join it simply because I dont have that kind of money to throw away. $40 a month buys me better things in life than a premium service game. <br><br>It's too hard to predict if this Legends idea will succeed or not. Hang tight people. I think everyone is in mass hysteria mode right now. <br><br>P.S. -- I do agree with Rexfelix on one point. The EQ Legends server is partially a trial run phase (economic model) for what may be incorporated into Verant's upcoming Star Wars Galaxies. <br><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaladominus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maladominus</A> at: 2/2/02 6:20:23 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usoneldarblackrose.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Soneldar Blackrose</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 102<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/2/02 6:21:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1265.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Alright...</span><hr size=1> &quot;I also don't buy into the &quot;decline phase&quot; theory&quot;<br><br>You can't: they revoked the server pop numbers, remember? <p>Soneldar Blackrose<br><b>1 of 9 of the Council of Fate, 1st Fist of Light</b><br><i>"All gold does not glitter<br>     Not all who wander are lost"</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uroninsenshi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RoninSenshi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/sageofthehalo/Kanji.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senshi No Adakia</span><br>  Posts: 367<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/2/02 7:03:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1265.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/sageofthehalo/Kanji.jpg WIDT